## `shouldRevalidate`

Pass `shouldRevalidate: false` when the client already updates UI optimistically (timeline entries, local lists) and the server cache for that resource does not need invalidation.

Pass `true` or omit (defaults to `true`) when the action should call `revalidateTag()` â€” the tag itself depends on which data changed (`deal-history`, `deal-docs`, `get-deal-by-id-${dealId}`, etc.). See [validated-actions](validated-actions.mdc).

## Adding new messages

Add reusable copy to `src/constants/ui/toast.ts` instead of inline strings. Reference constants in tests with quoted names (e.g. `"TOAST_MESSAGES.SAVE_SUCCESS"`).

